---
const handOver = [
  'Account email, billing records, and IP addresses we have logged',
  'Encrypted file blobs (ciphertext)',
  'Metadata: file sizes, timestamps, sharing relationships',
  'Encrypted filenames (ciphertext, not readable)',
];

const cannotHandOver = [
  'Decrypted file contents',
  'Original filenames',
  'Your master key, password, or recovery phrase',
  'Any means by which we could decrypt the ciphertext',
];
---

<section id="legal" class="security-section alt" data-security-section>
  <div class="security-container">
    <div class="security-kicker">
      <div class="bb-eyebrow">Legal compulsion</div>
      <h2 class="bb-display-l">What we’ll do when asked.</h2>
      <p>
        We don’t pretend to be above the law. We just made sure the law can’t
        extract what we don’t have.
      </p>
    </div>

    <article class="legal-panel">
      <header>
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3 6 5 6 21 6"></path><path d="M19 6V20a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V6"></path><path d="M8 6V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h4a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v2"></path></svg>
        Our position
      </header>
      <div class="legal-body">
        <p class="lead">
          We comply with valid legal requests from EU authorities.
          We do not comply with requests that lack a legal basis under EU law.
        </p>
        <p>When we receive a valid request, we hand over what we have:</p>
        <ul class="security-list">
          {handOver.map((item) => (
            <li><span class="bullet"></span><span>{item}</span></li>
          ))}
        </ul>
        <p>What we do not have, and therefore cannot hand over:</p>
        <ul class="security-list">
          {cannotHandOver.map((item) => (
            <li><span class="bullet amber"></span><span>{item}</span></li>
          ))}
        </ul>
        <div class="backdoor-note">
          <strong>If we’re asked to add a backdoor:</strong>
          we will refuse, contest it through every legal avenue, and — if
          ultimately compelled — disclose it publicly to the extent the law allows.
          No ongoing user can be silently downgraded.
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .legal-panel {
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: var(--paper);
  }

  .legal-panel header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 24px 32px;
    background: var(--ink);
    color: oklch(0.95 0.005 80);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .legal-panel header svg {
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
  }

  .legal-body {
    padding: 32px;
  }

  .legal-body p {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .legal-body p:not(.lead):nth-of-type(2) {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-body .lead {
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: 17px;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .security-list + p {
    margin-top: 24px;
  }

  .backdoor-note {
    margin-top: 28px;
    padding: 16px 18px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--paper-2);
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 13.5px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .backdoor-note strong {
    color: var(--ink);
  }
</style>
